# Git: branches and releases

## Branches

- `main` is production. Never commit directly unless the user explicitly asks.
- New branches from `main`: `feat/*`, `fix/*`, `chore/*`, `release/*`.
- PRs to `main`; title `[better-screenshoot] …`.

## Commits

- Conventional Commits: `feat:`, `fix:`, `chore:`, `docs:`, `ci:`.
- One PR = one goal. Don't mix feature + version bump without reason.

## Versions

Sync across all these files when bumping version:

- `Cargo.toml` (`[workspace.package].version`)
- `package.json` (root and monorepo packages)
- `apps/desktop/src-tauri/tauri.conf.json`

## Releases

- Semver tag from `main`: `v0.2.0`.
- The `.github/workflows/release.yml` workflow creates a draft release when pushing `v*`.
- See `docs/branching.md` for the full flow.
